<div class="about-wrapper">
    <div class="about-content">
        <p class="dropcap">Hello, I'm David. I like to take photographs in my free time. I try to spend as much time outdoors as possible, so most of my photographs are landscapes. 
            I work as a DevOps Engineer and find being outside with my camera(s) a great way to balance things. 
            The photographs on this site were taken with a variety of cameras, most of them analog. Using less CPU-time in my life is nice.</p>
        <p>The majority of my photographs are taken around Switzerland. A few are from Scandinavia or further away (from me at least :P). 
            This site serves two purposes. Primarily, it is meant as a replacement for my old Instagram account, which I do not maintain anymore. I have better ways to spend my time than doomscrolling through that misbegotten app. 
            Friends and family can enjoy my photography here, and everyone else. If you happen to find it :).
            The second purpose is to act as a photographic diary, where I keep my favorite shots in one place.
            There are dedicated tools for this, but I like this site. I will add some metadata to my photographs in the future, but for now you can just enjoy the images as they are. Done is better than perfect.</p>
        
            
